<HEAD>River Overflows, Leaving Two Dead, 12 Missing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CARACAS, Venezuela (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Heavy weekend rains sent a river over its banks and triggered a mudslide that destroyed nearly 100 houses in a coastal resort and left two people dead and 12 missing, officials said. The Chichiriviche river overflowed after a downpour Saturday night, causing a mudslide that covered several of the houses `` up to their roofs,'' civilian <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> Director <PERSON> Freddy </PERSON> <PERSON> Paris </PERSON> told the official news agency <ORGANIZATION> Venpres </ORGANIZATION>. `` There is mud up to five meters -LRB- yards -RRB- high. It is likely there are more victims in there and we are working to find those missing,'' he said Sunday. <LOCATION> Paris </LOCATION> said the houses belonged to people vacationing in the <LOCATION> Caribbean </LOCATION> resort 25 miles north of <LOCATION> Caracas </LOCATION> near <LOCATION> La </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Guaira </LOCATION> port. The flooding was the worst since last September, when a mudslide caused by a downpour in another coastal area killed hundreds of vacationers.
