<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Insisting Lt. Col. <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Higgins </PERSON> used his <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nations </ORGANIZATION> post as a cover to spy for the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, a pro-Iranian extremist group rejected a <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> appeal for the American hostage's release. <PERSON> Abbas </PERSON> <PERSON> Mousawi </PERSON>, a senior leader of the <ORGANIZATION> Shiite </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Moslem </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hezbollah </ORGANIZATION>, or Party of God, said Sunday that the group considers the <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> resolution `` part of a plot against the Moslems and <ORGANIZATION> Mujahedeen </ORGANIZATION> -LRB- holy warriors -RRB- of this area.'' `` We consider the arrest of this agent by the sons of this nation as part of its defense of its dignity and existence,'' <PERSON> Mousawi </PERSON> said at a rally in the southeastern town of <LOCATION> Mashgara </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Hezbollah </ORGANIZATION> is believed to be an umbrella group for <ORGANIZATION> Shiite </ORGANIZATION> factions holding most of the 18 foreign hostages, including nine Americans, in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Mousawi </PERSON>'s speech was the first <ORGANIZATION> Hezbollah </ORGANIZATION> reply to resolution passed unanimously Friday by the 15-nation <ORGANIZATION> Security </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> condemning the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Marine </ORGANIZATION>'s abduction and pleading for his immediate release. <PERSON> Higgins </PERSON>, 43, of <LOCATION> Danville </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ky. </LOCATION>, was chief of a 76-member observer group attached to the <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Interim </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> when he was abducted Feb. 17. The <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION> veteran al