<HEAD>Singleton's Victim Marries 10 Years After Attack</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MODESTO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The woman whose forearms were chopped off after she was raped 10 years ago by <PERSON> Lawrence </PERSON> <PERSON> Singleton </PERSON> and left for dead has gotten married. <PERSON> Mary </PERSON> <PERSON> Vincent </PERSON>, 25, and landscaper <PERSON> Matthew </PERSON> <PERSON> Brockman </PERSON>, 23, were wed Saturday in the presence of 75 guests, including her 2-year-old son, <PERSON> Luke </PERSON>, the Modesto Bee reported. The location of the wedding was n't disclosed. It has been reported previously that after speaking out publicly about the rape, <PERSON> Miss </PERSON> <PERSON> Vincent </PERSON> sought privacy in the <LOCATION> Pacific </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Northwest </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Singleton </PERSON>, 60, was convicted of raping Miss <PERSON> Vincent </PERSON> and hacking off her arms with an ax after picking up the 15-year-old hitchhiker in September 1978. She was found abandoned and left for dead in a rural area. He repeatedly proclaimed his innocence and was released from prison in 1987. <PERSON> Singleton </PERSON> spent his parole in a trailer on the grounds of <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Quentin </LOCATION> <LOCATION> State </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Prison </LOCATION> after his planned parole to a town about 20 miles northeast of <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION> was met with protests. He was freed in April.
