ashlight in the eyes of a sleeping 10-year-old boy, and forced the boy at knifepoint to leave with him, <LOCATION> Burlingame </LOCATION> said. The boy's parents were sleeping. The child was molested and then released to find his way home, <LOCATION> Burlingame </LOCATION> said. Later Friday, a man tried to abduct an 11-year-old girl in <LOCATION> Bellingham </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mass. </LOCATION>, police said. He grabbed the girl by the arm, but she broke free, and he drove off. The man returned to <LOCATION> Rhode </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Island </LOCATION>, pulling the 6-year-old off the sidewalk two blocks from his home, police said. That abduction triggered a search of the <LOCATION> Warwick </LOCATION> area by about 125 local, state and federal authorities, aided by civilian groups. When the boy was returned, police chased the suspect who fled by car and then on foot. <LOCATION> Burlingame </LOCATION> said all three children have identified <PERSON> Gardner </PERSON>. The detective also said police in several other communities are interested in questioning <PERSON> Gardner </PERSON> in connection with abductions within the last six weeks. In the <LOCATION> Hingham </LOCATION> case, <PERSON> Gardner </PERSON> pleaded guilty June 2 to abducting a 12-year-old boy in November 1987, tying him to a tree in a state park and molesting him. Mrs. <PERSON> Gardner </PERSON>, who lives in <LOCATION> Weymouth </LOCATION>, said her son was `` a confused child who was raped when he was 12.'' <PERSON> Steve </PERSON> <PERSON> Hudson </PERSON>, 17, who lives near the <ORGANIZATION> Gardners </ORGANIZATION> in the middle-class neighborhood near downtown <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION>, called <PERSON> Gardner </PERSON> `` an introverted person.'' `` He always hung around by himself. He never had any friends his own age, never any girlfriends or anything like that. No one his own age ever went near him,'' <PERSON> Hudson </PERSON> said. `` He was like a social outcast.''
