s for promotions. <PERSON> Swartz </PERSON> and the company later said the supervisor had not cursed <PERSON> Swartz </PERSON>, and <ORGANIZATION> UPS </ORGANIZATION> praised the driver's actions, saying the collision would not be charged against his record. The company honored <PERSON> Swartz </PERSON> for heroism at a reception June 24. In Friday's hearing, <ORGANIZATION> Jefferson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Judge </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Robert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Morris </ORGANIZATION> concluded there was sufficient evidence to try both suspects on six counts each of aggravated robbery and one count each of felony menacing. The men, both held on $ 100,000 bonds, are to be arraigned Aug. 15 in <LOCATION> Jefferson </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> <LOCATION> District </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Court </LOCATION>.
