meson </PERSON> case,'' <PERSON> Kozloski </PERSON> said. `` This is purely an administrative action. No one is being punished merely for testifying. <PERSON> Gurule </PERSON> and <PERSON> Hilinski </PERSON> testified they would be willing to work with Ms. <PERSON> Jameson </PERSON>. `` The fact is that if a Marine in a position of high responsibility such as a drill instructor makes a statement under oath that -LRB- shows -RRB- he or she does n't understand or support an order directly governing his or her duties, it is within the discretion of the commander to consider removing that individual from that specific postion.'' Ms. <PERSON> DiBattiste </PERSON> said that although officers could be court-martialed if found guilty of engaging in illegal command influence, such charges are usually dropped. `` All I can tell you is I think that's an appropriate allegation for defense council to make,'' Ms. <PERSON> DiBattiste </PERSON> said. `` I would not render an opinion to you whether they would win or lose.''
