Jo </PERSON> <PERSON> Barnier </PERSON> said 682 firefighters had completed lines around 90 percent of the fire. A <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> man accused of starting that fire appeared in court Monday on a misdemeanor charge of allowing a camp fire to escape, <PERSON> Barnier </PERSON> said. Low temperatures and high humidity helped efforts to contain three fires burning in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> state, said <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Natural </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Resources </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Forest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> officials. The largest, the 3,600-acre <LOCATION> Falls </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Creek </LOCATION> fire, was 90 percent contained, said <ORGANIZATION> Forest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> spokeswoman <PERSON> Kathy </PERSON> <PERSON> Albert </PERSON>. A 55-acre fire on the Olympic Peninsula near <LOCATION> Hoquiam </LOCATION> was under control and firefighters had almost suppressed a 75-acre blaze near <LOCATION> Skykomish </LOCATION>, officials said. High wind Monday morning in <LOCATION> Oregon </LOCATION> hampered efforts to contain an 145-acre fire in the <ORGANIZATION> Mount </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hood </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Forest </ORGANIZATION>, but spokeswoman <PERSON> Jane </PERSON> <PERSON> Cottrell </PERSON> said a line had been built around 95 percent of the fire. She said firefighters expect to have it contained by Tuesday. A three-mile section of a <ORGANIZATION> Forest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> road was closed as officials expressed concern for the safety of mountain bikers who had been seen in the vicinity, <PERSON> Cottrell </PERSON> said. In southern <LOCATION> Oregon </LOCATION>, firefighters contained nearly 90 small blazes Sunday on private and public la