 `` Raw'' -LRB- <ORGANIZATION> Paramount </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Video </ORGANIZATION>; VHS _ $ 89.95, Beta _ $ 29.95; Rated R -RRB- `` Raw'' is the technical result of an <PERSON> Eddie </PERSON> <PERSON> Murphy </PERSON> performance at <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>'s Felt Forum, and it is aptly titled. It seems that <PERSON> Murphy </PERSON> went to the <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Pryor </PERSON> school of comedy and emerged with a doctorate in dirtyspeak. The video opens at a family Thanksgiving gathering in the 1960s. After dinner, a few of the youngsters give a talent show for their adoring parents. <PERSON> Eddie </PERSON> the child tells a scatological joke, raising eyebrows from the grownups and providing a fast seque to 1987 and his stage show. <PERSON> Murphy </PERSON>'s routines are pat and almost formula by now, with predictable swipes at women, marriage, sex, homosexuals and various ethnic groups. Occasionally, he's funny. He gives a great imitation of <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Cosby </PERSON>, who allegedly called him on the phone one day to tell him that dirty words do not a comic make. He also does good impersonations of Mr. T and <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Pryor </PERSON>. `` Raw,'' however, is strictly for connoisseurs of <PERSON> Eddie </PERSON> <PERSON> Murphy </PERSON>'s brash narcissism
