<HEAD>AP WEEKEND ENTERTAINMENT AND ARTS</HEAD>
<HEAD>In the Groove: Record Review</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By PAUL RAEBURN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 `` Panther -LRB- Yauarete -RRB-'' -LRB- <ORGANIZATION> Columbia </ORGANIZATION> -RRB- _ <PERSON> Milton </PERSON> <PERSON> Nascimento </PERSON> <PERSON> Milton </PERSON> <PERSON> Nascimento </PERSON> has a unique ability to combine primitive, folk-like melodies with sophisticated, jazz-inspired harmonies. The result is music of unusual depth and complexity, with moods ranging from jubilant to mournful. `` Yauarete'' contains a diverse collection of Nascimento's latest compositions It can be listened to either as a showcase of those compositions, or as the evocative performance of one of <LOCATION> Brazil </LOCATION>'s most moving singers. On the one hand, the freshness and originality of the 11 songs on the album attest to <PERSON> Nascimento </PERSON>'s seemingly inexhaustible creative energy and the breadth of his talent. `` Meu Mestre Coracao -LRB- Heart Is My Master -RRB-,'' a deftly engaging bossa nova, follows a meditative excursion entitled `` Cidade Encantada -LRB- Enchanted City -RRB-.'' `` Cancoes E Moments -LRB- Songs and Moments -RRB-'' is a short, repeating refrain that <PERSON> Nascimento </PERSON> has recently used as a closing number during live performances, leaving the audience quietly singing it as he and the band gradually drift offstage. Each song on the record is different, and each reveals another facet of Nascimento's compositional skill Even if <PERSON> Nascimento </PERSON> had n't written the songs, however, this album would be remarkable merely for his performances. His voice is rough but powerful, and it is often tinged with a bittersweet longing. With one exception, the songs on `` Yauarete'' are sung in Portuguese, but the feeling in <LOCATION> Nascimento </LOCATION>'s voice carries across the language barrier. <ORGANIZATION> Columbia </ORGANIZATION> has, however, printed English translations alongside the Portuguese lyrics on the album's inner sleeve. -LRB- Nascimento works closely with several lyricists who generally supply the words to go with his music. -RRB-
