<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Lorimar </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Telepictures </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> said Monday it has sold three network-affiliated television stations in <LOCATION> California </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Missouri </LOCATION> for a total of $ 23 million. The previously announced transaction included stations KCMP-TV, <LOCATION> Chico-Redding </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>; KMID-TV, <LOCATION> Midland-Odessa </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>; and <ORGANIZATION> KSPR-TV </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> Springfield </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mo </LOCATION>. The buyer was Goltrin Acquisition Partnership, whose principals are <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Goldfarb </PERSON>, a former <ORGANIZATION> Lorimar </ORGANIZATION> executive; <PERSON> Barbara </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Goldfarb </PERSON>, a <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> attorney, and <PERSON> Melvyn </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Estrin </PERSON>, chairman of <ORGANIZATION> Human </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, a <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> D.C. </LOCATION>, financial investment and management services company.. <ORGANIZATION> KCMP </ORGANIZATION> is an <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> affiliate; KMID and <ORGANIZATION> KSPR </ORGANIZATION> are <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> affiliates
